						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying in the Lingamayya shrine behind the Śiva temple.</p>						

						<p>Vijayanagara; Achyutadēva.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1461, Vikāri, Āshāḍha śu. 11,</hi> corresponding to 1539 A.D., June 27, Friday.</p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. It seems to register certain grants of land made by Pāpināynaningāru along with his wife Pāpasāni son of Goḍugumari Bhūmināyuḍu at the village Kanyalūru granted to them by Salakarāju Peda Tirumala rāju.</p>						

						</summary>
